HUFRISH sent an attachment.
Male giraffes use a mix of chemistry and strength to find a mate. Their process seems unusual, but each step works for life on the open savanna. To learn if a female is ready to mate, a male tests her urine. He takes a small sample with his tongue and uses a behavior called the Flehmen response. He curls his lip and pulls the scent into a special organ in his mouth that reads chemical signals. These signals tell him if the female is fertile. If she is, he stays close. If not, he keeps moving. Males also compete through necking, a fight where they swing their long necks and hit each other with their heads. The harder and more controlled the strikes, the more dominance a male shows. The winner earns the chance to stay near fertile females. Females help guide the process too. Some will urinate when a favored male approaches, which signals interest. By using chemical cues and physical contests, giraffes solve the challenge of finding mates in large, spread-out habitats.

Prairie dogs are naturally social animals that live in colonies and often display close physical bonds with one another. Their behaviors include cuddling, grooming, and vocal communication, all of which strengthen ties within the group and provide comfort. These interactions are essential to their survival in the wild, as cooperation helps them detect predators and maintain their complex burrow systems. The image of two prairie dogs curled up together highlights this instinct for connection. While their embrace may simply be a display of warmth and security, it resonates with people as a symbol of companionship. Their closeness reflects the kind of comfort and trust that many associate with strong relationships, making the moment feel both endearing and deeply relatable.

Dabeli ‚ú® üìùIngredients:- Sweet chutney: 2 tbsp cup tamarind pulp ¬º cup sugar syrup ¬Ω cup water Red chilly-Garlic chutney: 10 red chillies soaked in water 6-8 garlic cloves 3 tbsp water Salt as required Dabeli mix: 2 dry red chili 1 tsp coriander seeds ¬Ω inch stick cinnamon 2 to 3 cloves ¬Ω teaspoon cumin seeds A pinch asafoetida Garnish: 5 tbsp corriander leaves 5 tbsp pomegranate seeds Masala peanuts: ¬º cup Roasted peanuts ¬Ω tsp oil ¬Ω tsp dabeli masala ¬Ω tsp sugar Pinch of salt Assembly: 6 Pav 2 tbsp butter ¬Ω cup onion ¬º cup Sev Method: * Dabeli Mix: In a medium hot pan, add coriander seeds, cumin seeds, dry red chillies, cinnamon sticks, cloves and roast till fragrant. Once roasted, add asafoetida and turn the flame off. Transfer the roasted masala to another container and let it cool to room temperature. After 10-12 minutes grind these spices finely. * Chilli-Garlic Chutney: Take the soaked red chillies, garlic and salt and grind it to a smooth paste initially and then add water to make a thick paste. Once grinded, transfer the paste to a bowl and thin it down as required by adding water. * Sweet Chutney: Take water in a pan and add in sugar, tamarind pulp and let it cook for 3-5 minutes. Once cooked, allow it to cool down to room temperature. * Mashed Potatoes Mix: In the same pan heat some oil and add in the Dabeli Spice Mix and stir on a medium flame and add boiled mashed potatoes and mix it well. Add salt as required and then add sweet chutney . Allow this cook for 2-3 minutes on moderate flame and transfer it to a plate and flatten it. Garnish with coriander leaves and pomegranate seeds. * Masala Peanuts: Add some oil, Dabeli Spice Mix and sugar to roasted potatoes and mix it well. Add salt as required. * The Assembly:- Slice the Bun-Paav in half, then stuff it with sweet chutney, chilli-garlic chutney, mashed potatoes mix, onions, masala peanuts & dip it into the sev. Heat a pan and roast the Dabeli with butter till crisp on both the sides. üëë Dangi Patis: Pune‚Äôs Legendary Bread Patis! If you talk about iconic Pune street food, Dangi Patis is the name that immediately comes up. This place has been serving its famous deep-fried bread patties since 1972, and it‚Äôs a true institution in the city! These aren‚Äôt just any bread pakoras‚Äîthey are legendary. Two slices of soft bread are generously stuffed with a perfectly spiced potato filling (masala aloo), dipped in a besan (chickpea flour) batter, and fried until golden and crunchy. Served with simple fried green chillies, the combination of the crispy exterior and the soft, flavorful stuffing inside is just incredible. What makes Dangi Patis special is their focus: they only serve one thing, and they do it to perfection. They open for very limited hours‚Äîa few hours in the morning and a short window in the evening‚Äîso you know the long queues are worth it for this classic Maharashtrian snack! We absolutely loved this quintessential Food of Pune, and seeing our little one, Amaira, enjoy it the most was the sweetest part. A must-try for every food lover visiting Pune! Have you experienced the Dangi Patis magic? Like this content? Follow us @answerallquestions for more ‚ù§Ô∏è When people cuddle, their brains release oxytocin, often called the ‚Äúlove hormone,‚Äù which creates feelings of comfort, bonding, and emotional security. Over time, the brain adjusts to these elevated hormone levels, reinforcing the sense of connection and making physical closeness feel rewarding and necessary. This chemical response is why cuddling can strengthen relationships and make partners feel more deeply attached to one another. However, when separated, the sudden drop in oxytocin can leave individuals feeling restless, lonely, or even anxious, almost like experiencing withdrawal. The brain, accustomed to the steady ‚Äúdose‚Äù of bonding hormones, begins to crave the comfort and closeness it associates with physical affection. This is why some people find it especially hard to be apart from those they regularly cuddle, as the body and mind both yearn to restore that sense of warmth and connection. Studies have revealed that cuddling and other forms of loving physical contact can influence gene expression through a process called epigenetics, which helps turn off genes linked to chronic diseases and activate repair genes. Epigenetics refers to changes that affect how your genes are expressed-effectively turning them on or off-without altering the underlying DNA sequence. Physical touch can alter gene expression through several biological mechanisms: **HORMONAL SHIFTS: Cuddling and affectionate touch lead to the release of beneficial hormones and neurotransmitters, including oxytocin and serotonin, while reducing the stress hormone cortisol. **REDUCED INFLAMMATION: The hormonal shifts that result from physical touch can promote anti-inflammatory pathways in the body. HUFRISH sent an attachment.
Clingy cats often surprise people who expect felines to be aloof and independent. While many cats enjoy their alone time, some form very strong bonds with their favorite humans and like to stay close‚Äîsometimes very close. A clingy cat may follow you from room to room, curl up on your lap the moment you sit down, or meow loudly when you‚Äôre out of sight. This behavior usually comes from affection and trust; your cat has decided you‚Äôre their safe place. There are many reasons a cat might become clingy. Some cats have more social or affectionate personalities, while others develop clinginess because of changes in their environment, like moving homes, new pets, or shifts in routine. Kittens that were orphaned or separated from their mothers too early may also seek extra reassurance as adults. In some cases, clingy behavior is simply a cat showing that they feel comfortable and bonded‚Äîbut it can also be a sign of anxiety or insecurity. Living with a clingy cat can be both sweet and challenging. On one hand, it‚Äôs heartwarming to have a furry companion who wants constant affection and companionship. On the other hand, clinginess can become overwhelming if your cat demands attention at inconvenient times or becomes distressed when you‚Äôre not home. Providing enrichment‚Äîsuch as toys, climbing spaces, and consistent routines‚Äîcan help your cat feel more secure and less dependent on constant closeness. Ultimately, clinginess in cats is just one way they express love and attachment. While every cat is different, many clingy cats simply want reassurance that their favorite person is nearby and that the bond they‚Äôve formed is safe. With patience and understanding, their neediness can become a charming part of their personality rather than a problem.#cat #fyp #cutekitty #viralreels

Red pandas are small, tree-dwelling mammals native to the eastern Himalayas and parts of China, instantly recognisable for their fluffy red fur, bushy tails, and fondness for bamboo. Despite their charm, they face severe threats in the wild, including deforestation, poaching, and fragmented habitats that make finding food or mates difficult. In captivity, however, they fare much better. Zoos and sanctuaries offer safe habitats, steady food supplies, medical care, and participate in breeding programs aimed at protecting the species. As a result, red pandas often live longer and thrive more in captivity than they do in their natural environments. A short video capturing the reaction of a hedgehog to the smell of an apple has gained attention online for its unusual display of animal behavior. When the fruit is placed nearby, the hedgehog reacts with visible agitation, curling slightly and showing signs of discomfort. Instead of curiosity, the animal appears irritated, as if the scent were unwelcome or too strong. Researchers note that hedgehogs have highly developed senses of smell, which they rely on to navigate their environment, find food, and avoid danger. Certain scents, however, can trigger defensive or aggressive responses, and the sharp, acidic aroma of apples may be one of them. The behavior highlights how even common household items can produce unexpected effects in animals with sensitive olfactory systems. While the clip may seem humorous at first, it also offers a reminder of the importance of understanding animal sensitivities. Everyday smells that humans barely notice can provoke strong reactions in other species. In this case, the apple became more than just a piece of fruit‚Äîit acted as a stimulus that revealed a hedgehog‚Äôs instinctive defenses.

In 2025, Austin, Texas became the first U.S. city to pilot PawPrint Power Paths, a renewable-energy initiative that transforms every dog walk into a power source. Each walkway tile is built with piezoelectric materials, which convert pressure from footsteps and paw steps into small electrical charges. The harvested energy is then stored and used to power park lighting, benches, and smart sensors. The system was first installed in Zilker Dog Park, covering about 4,000 square feet of pathways ‚Äî effectively turning one of Austin‚Äôs busiest pet areas into a micro-power plant fueled by daily activity. The project reflects Austin‚Äôs growing reputation as a hub for green technology and smart urban innovation, and if successful, could be expanded to sidewalks, campuses, and public squares nationwide.
